gency Management|url=http://www.rappahannockcountyva.gov/documents/200317%20SIGNED%20Rapp%20Declaration%20of%20Local%20Emergency.pdf|title=Declaration Of A Local State of Emergency|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Washington, Virginia]]|publisher=[[Rappahannock County, Virginia|Rappahannock County]] Government: County Administrator's Office|accessdate=March 29, 2020|quote= ... acting as Director of Emergency Management, I, Garrey W. Curry, Jr., excercise the authority given to me under Code of Virginia \u00a7 44-146.21 to declare a local state of emergency that shall remain in effect until rescinded by a subsequent order; ...}}</ref> [[Spotsylvania County, Virginia|Spotsylvania County]] declared a local state of emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spotsylvania.va.us/CivicAlerts.aspx?AID=162|title=State Of Emergency Declaration COVID-19|work=Press Release|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Spotsylvania Courthouse, Virginia|Spotsylvania, Virginia]]|publisher=[[Spotsylvania County, Virginia]],  Government|accessdate=March 29, 2020|quote=Spotsylvania County declares a local state of emergency in response to growing concerns over the spread of Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19). County Administrator Edward Petrovitch made the announcement Tuesday evening, March 17, 2020, during a special meeting of the Board of Supervisors.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327030727/https://spotsylvania.va.us/CivicAlerts.aspx?AID=162|archive-date=March 27, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Clarke County, Virginia|Clarke County]] Board of Supervisors adopted a declaration of local emergency.<ref>{{cite web|first=Mickey|last=Powell|date=March 18, 2020|url=https://www.winchesterstar.com/coronavirus/coronavirus-prompts-clarke-county-to-declare-emergency/article_f448b813-29a0-569d-9a9f-f7945d63fd71.html|title=Coronavirus prompts Clarke County to declare emergency|location=[[Winchester, Virginia]]|publisher=[[The Winchester Star]]|accessdate=March 29, 2020|quote=A local emergency declaration was adopted by the Clarke County Board of Supervisors in a unanimous vote Tuesday afternoon. .... The declaration also enables the county, if it eventually becomes necessary, to \"control, restrict, allocate or regulate the use, sale, production or distribution of food, fuel, clothing and other commodities, materials, goods, services and resource systems which fall only within the boundaries\" of Clarke County and do not affect nearby localities.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318133347/https://www.winchesterstar.com/coronavirus/coronavirus-prompts-clarke-county-to-declare-emergency/article_f448b813-29a0-569d-9a9f-f7945d63fd71.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Culpeper County, Virginia|Culpeper County]] Board of Supervisors declared a local state of emergency.<ref>(1) {{cite news|url=https://www.starexponent.com/news/culpeper-county-declares-local-state-of-emergency/article_ac4692c4-133b-5fbd-9943-6239093d332f.html|title=Culpeper County declares local state of emergency|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Culpeper, Virginia]]|publisher=Culpeper Star-Exponent|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}<br>(2) {{cite news|first=Pat|last=Fitzgerald|date=March 26, 2020|url=https://www.insidenova.com/culpeper/culpeper-officials-give-board-of-supervisors-update-on-virus-response/article_8b9c37e6-6f63-11ea-b045-1756af02e577.html|title=Culpeper officials give Board of Supervisors update on virus response|work=Culpeper Times|publisher=InsideNoVa.com|accessdate=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329045559/https://www.insidenova.com/culpeper/culpeper-officials-give-board-of-supervisors-update-on-virus-response/article_8b9c37e6-6f63-11ea-b045-1756af02e577.html|archive-date=March 29, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Warren County, Virginia|Warren County]] Local Director of Emergency Management issued a declaration of local emergency, to which the County's Board of Supervisors consented on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|