-county-declares-local-state-of-emergency/article_5509deba-6aed-11ea-b811-1fbe69069993.html|title=Fairfax County declares local state of emergency|work=[[Fairfax Times|Fairfax County Times]]|location=[[Sterling, Virginia]]|publisher=Fairfax County Times|accessdate=March 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327051755/http://www.fairfaxtimes.com/articles/fairfax-county-declares-local-state-of-emergency/article_5509deba-6aed-11ea-b811-1fbe69069993.html|archive-date=March 27, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Rappahannock County, Virginia|Rappahannock County]] Administrator, acting as the Director of Emergency Management, declared a local state of emergency.<ref>{{cite web|last=Curry, Jr.|first=Garrey W., Director of Emergency Management|url=http://www.rappahannockcountyva.gov/documents/200317%20SIGNED%20Rapp%20Declaration%20of%20Local%20Emergency.pdf|title=Declaration Of A Local State of Emergency|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Washington, Virginia]]|publisher=[[Rappahannock County, Virginia|Rappahannock County]] Government: County Administrator's Office|accessdate=March 29, 2020|quote= ... acting as Director of Emergency Management, I, Garrey W. Curry, Jr., excercise the authority given to me under Code of Virginia \u00a7 44-146.21 to declare a local state of emergency that shall remain in effect until rescinded by a subsequent order; ...}}</ref> [[Spotsylvania County, Virginia|Spotsylvania County]] declared a local state of emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spotsylvania.va.us/CivicAlerts.aspx?AID=162|title=State Of Emergency Declaration COVID-19|work=Press Release|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Spotsylvania Courthouse, Virginia|Spotsylvania, Virginia]]|publisher=[[Spotsylvania County, Virginia]],  Government|accessdate=March 29, 2020|quote=Spotsylvania County declares a local state of emergency in response to growing concerns over the spread of Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19). County Administrator Edward Petrovitch made the announcement 