per/culpeper-officials-give-board-of-supervisors-update-on-virus-response/article_8b9c37e6-6f63-11ea-b045-1756af02e577.html|title=Culpeper officials give Board of Supervisors update on virus response|work=Culpeper Times|publisher=InsideNoVa.com|accessdate=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329045559/https://www.insidenova.com/culpeper/culpeper-officials-give-board-of-supervisors-update-on-virus-response/article_8b9c37e6-6f63-11ea-b045-1756af02e577.html|archive-date=March 29, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Warren County, Virginia|Warren County]] Local Director of Emergency Management issued a declaration of local emergency, to which the County's Board of Supervisors consented on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mabe|first=Walter J., Local Director of Emergency Management/Chairman, Warren County Board of Supervisors|date=March 17, 2020|url=https://www.warrencountyva.net/images/Declaration_-_Local_State_of_Emergency_COVID-19.pdf|title=Declaration of Local Emergency by the Local Director of Emergency Management and Consent of the Board of Supervisors of Warren County|location=[[Front Royal, Virginia]]|publisher=[[Warren County, Virginia]] Government|accessdate=March 29, 2020|quote=THEREFORE, the Chairman of the Board of Supervisors, Walter J. Mabe, is the Local Director of Emergency Management (the \"Local Director\") and declares that a local emergency exists in Warren County pursuant to Code of Virginia \u00a7 44-146.21. THEREFORE, the Warren County Board of Supervisors consents to the Local Director's declaration of local emergency pursuant to Code of Virginia \u00a7 44-146.21.}}</ref> The [[Page County, Virginia|Page County]] Board of Supervisors approved a resolution containing a declaration of a local emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pagecounty.virginia.gov/DocumentCenter/View/2468/PageCountyLocalEmergencyDeclaration_COVID19|title=Resolution: Declaration Of A Local Emergency|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Luray, Virginia]]|publisher=[[Page County, Virginia]], Government|accessdate=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329213122/https://www.pagecounty.virginia.gov/DocumentCenter/View/2468/PageCountyLocalEmergencyDeclaration_COVID19|archive-date=March 29, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Shenandoah County, Virginia|Shenandoah County]] Administrator declared a local emergency, which the County's Board of Supervisors was scheduled to ratify on March 24.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shenandoahcountyva.us/administration/2020/03/shenandoah-county-declares-local-emergency/|title=Shenandoah County Declares Local Emergency|work=Media Release|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Woodstock, Virginia]]|publisher=[[Shenandoah County, Virginia]] Government|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref> The Mayor and City Council of the [[Fairfax, Virginia|City of Fairfax]] adopted a declaration of local emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fairfaxva.gov/Home/Components/News/News/9914/18|title=Declaration of Local Emergency - COVID 19, City of Fairfax, Virginia|work=News|date=March 18, 2020|publisher=[[Fairfax, Virginia|City of Fairfax, Virginia]] Government|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> The [[Manassas, Virginia|Manassas]] City Manager signed a declaration of local state of emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidenova.com/news/prince_william/local/manassas/manassas-declares-state-of-emergency/article_cfb38be4-688f-11ea-a8a6-dbf655e65359.html|title=Manassas declares state of emergency|work=InsideNova|date=March 17, 2020|publisher=InsideNoVa.com|accessdate=March 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319200053/https://www.insidenova.com/news/prince_william/local/manassas/manassas-declares-state-of-emergency/article_cfb38be4-688f-11ea-a8a6-dbf655e65359.html|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The interim City Manager of [[Winchester, Virginia|Winchester]] declared a state of emergency for the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.winchesterva.gov/city-mana